✨🏆✨ Full 🔵 moment. 

Just found this and had to post.

A year ago, our lives were turned completely upside down. My husband was visiting Ukraine when Russia invaded. As a Ukrainian citizen, he was under the country’s native Martial Law, which meant as a male, he couldn’t leave and was required to report for military duty if called upon. Being a resident of the US, he was officially exempt, however, he needed to prove it to the Ukrainian government before he could return home -
but their government shut down, was then catching up for months, and he was stuck there until - he finally was able to return to us on New Years Eve! 

Our family is safe, though the situation is far from over. Friends and family are fighting. Last year, I created “A Ukrainian Love Story” as a tribute to him, his culture, and as a sort-of music therapy. We asked @j_ivy to write a poem for the tribute and I performed “Over The Rainbow.” We won an HMMA in November for our video. And J - He won a GRAMMY this year for his latest record, “The Poet Who Sat By The Door!” So inspired by you! 

At the GRAMMY’s, J and Andrii met for the first time. This is that moment. 🥹 🤗❤️

One of my late friends @nolannealmusic liked to say, “Maybe pain is gift.” When the sun comes out, the relief - and glory - is indescribable.

Keep your head up and keep chasing the ☀️light, my friends.

#GRAMMYWINNER #GRAMMYAWARDS2023 #tarralayne #hmmas2022 #aukrainianlovestory #overtherainbow #thepoetwhosatbythedoor #spokenwordpoetry

✨🔮🌸💪🏼✨Never felt more powerful.

.
.
.
.

So, hey! Surprise! I’ve been quiet ‘round here. So, um…here’s the real reel - a whole…lotta…preggo… just makin’ up for lost time (featuring “Glow Up Girl” - one of my fave tunes I wrote and performed with @notmaxmartin this past year for our project #GoGingerGoMusic). Just hangin’ in my closet and playing dress up with a bunch of clothes that def do not fit me at the moment, 😂. So, you got some casual, TLC meets who-knows, and a witchy cat-lady era I’m thriving in currently. (That’s Simba, our kitty, kitty.) 

Been v busy, grateful for it, and this year has been full of life, love, and incredible growth. I have a brand new, deeper respect for women, femininity, humanity, art, nature, mothers - and LIFE. Excited for new beginnings and this fresh fire 🔥 I’ve been feeding.

Our baby girl is due tomorrow - 12.12.23. Yes! Tomorrow! And I’m just sitting here waiting to see what she thinks about that. (Ey, let’s see if she’s ready.😉)

Happy holidaze, yinz.
